  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;Title&gt;Lovely staff but lacking organisation. &lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Vicky Lord&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;111 advised we attend A&amp;amp;E. My daughter was seen and xrayed within 20 mins but then waited another 3 hours to be told there was nothing broken and we could leave. The nurse was lovely and explained there was only one doctor on for the whole of A&amp;amp;E, I understand being short staffed. What I don't understand, is why a doctor can't look at multiple xrays and instruct the nurses to ask some people to stay and explain to others that there is nothing broken. When the doctor came through to the children's area, from telling me he was going to look at my daughters xray to telling us it was tendon damage and to go home took 4 minutes. There must be a more efficient way of letting people know there is nothing wrong. However, the staff were all lovely. &lt;/CommentText&gt;
